pokemon.name: turtwig
pokemon.text_entry: It undertakes photosynthesis with its body, making oxygen. The leaf on its head wilts if it is thirsty.

pokemon.name: grotle
pokemon.text_entry: It knows where pure water wells up. It carries fellow Pokémon there on its back.

pokemon.name: torterra
pokemon.text_entry: Small Pokémon occasionally gather on its unmoving back to begin building their nests.

pokemon.name: chimchar
pokemon.text_entry: The gas made in its belly burns from its rear end. The fire burns weakly when it feels sick.

pokemon.name: monferno
pokemon.text_entry: It uses ceilings and walls to launch aerial attacks. Its fiery tail is but one weapon.

pokemon.name: infernape
pokemon.text_entry: It tosses its enemies around with agility. It uses all its limbs to fight in its own unique style.

pokemon.name: piplup
pokemon.text_entry: Because it is very proud, it hates accepting food from people. Its thick down guards it from cold.

pokemon.name: prinplup
pokemon.text_entry: It lives a solitary life. Its wings deliver wicked blows that can snap even the thickest of trees.

pokemon.name: empoleon
pokemon.text_entry: The three horns that extend from its beak attest to its power. The leader has the biggest horns.

pokemon.name: starly
pokemon.text_entry: They flock around mountains and fields, chasing after bug Pokémon. Their singing is noisy and annoying.

pokemon.name: staravia
pokemon.text_entry: It lives in forests and fields. Squabbles over territory occur when flocks collide.

pokemon.name: staraptor
pokemon.text_entry: When Staravia evolve into Staraptor, they leave the flock to live alone. They have sturdy wings.

pokemon.name: bidoof
pokemon.text_entry: It constantly gnaws on logs and rocks to whittle down its front teeth. It nests alongside water.

pokemon.name: bibarel
pokemon.text_entry: It makes its nest by damming streams with bark and mud. It is known as an industrious worker.

pokemon.name: kricketot
pokemon.text_entry: When its antennae hit each other, it sounds like the music of a xylophone.

pokemon.name: kricketune
pokemon.text_entry: It signals its emotions with its melodies. Scientists are studying these melodic patterns.

pokemon.name: shinx
pokemon.text_entry: Electricity makes this Pokémon’s fur glow. Shinx sends signals to others of its kind by shaking the tip of its tail while the tail tip is shining brightly.

pokemon.name: luxio
pokemon.text_entry: Upon encountering an opponent, this Pokémon prepares for battle by extending its claws, which can put out 1,000,000 volts of electricity.

pokemon.name: luxray
pokemon.text_entry: Seeing through solid objects uses up a lot of Luxray’s electricity, so the Pokémon sleeps for long periods of time to store up energy.

pokemon.name: budew
pokemon.text_entry: This Pokémon is highly sensitive to temperature changes. When its bud starts to open, that means spring is right around the corner.

pokemon.name: roserade
pokemon.text_entry: The poison in its right hand is quick acting. The poison in its left hand is slow acting. Both are life threatening.

pokemon.name: cranidos
pokemon.text_entry: Its hard skull is its distinguishing feature. It snapped trees by headbutting them, and then it fed on their ripe berries.

pokemon.name: rampardos
pokemon.text_entry: This ancient Pokémon used headbutts skillfully. Its brain was really small, so some theories suggest that its stupidity led to its extinction.

pokemon.name: shieldon
pokemon.text_entry: Although its fossils can be found in layers of primeval rock, nothing but its face has ever been discovered.

pokemon.name: bastiodon
pokemon.text_entry: This Pokémon is from roughly 100 million years ago. Its terrifyingly tough face is harder than steel.

pokemon.name: burmy
pokemon.text_entry: If its cloak is broken in battle, it quickly remakes the cloak with materials nearby.

pokemon.name: wormadam-plant
pokemon.text_entry: When Burmy evolved, its cloak became a part of this Pokémon’s body. The cloak is never shed.

pokemon.name: mothim
pokemon.text_entry: It flutters around at night and steals honey from the Combee hive.

pokemon.name: combee
pokemon.text_entry: It ceaselessly gathers nectar from sunrise to sundown, all for the sake of Vespiquen and the swarm.

pokemon.name: vespiquen
pokemon.text_entry: Vespiquen that give off more pheromones have larger swarms of Combee attendants.

pokemon.name: pachirisu
pokemon.text_entry: A pair may be seen rubbing their cheek pouches together in an effort to share stored electricity.

pokemon.name: buizel
pokemon.text_entry: It inflates the flotation sac around its neck and pokes its head out of the water to see what is going on.

pokemon.name: floatzel
pokemon.text_entry: Its flotation sac developed as a result of pursuing aquatic prey. It can double as a rubber raft.

pokemon.name: cherubi
pokemon.text_entry: The deeper a Cherubi’s red, the more nutrients it has stockpiled in its body. And the sweeter and tastier its small ball!

pokemon.name: cherrim
pokemon.text_entry: The faint scent that emanates from its full blossom entices bug Pokémon to it.

pokemon.name: shellos
pokemon.text_entry: Subjecting this Pokémon to a strong force causes it to secrete a strange purple fluid. Though harmless, the fluid is awfully sticky.

pokemon.name: gastrodon
pokemon.text_entry: The softness of its body helps disperse the force of impacts, so although its body is uncommonly squishy, it’s also surprisingly resilient.

pokemon.name: ambipom
pokemon.text_entry: It uses its tails for everything. If it wraps both of its tails around you and gives you a squeeze, that’s proof it really likes you.

pokemon.name: drifloon
pokemon.text_entry: The gathering of many souls gave rise to this Pokémon. During humid seasons, they seem to appear in abundance.

pokemon.name: drifblim
pokemon.text_entry: It grabs people and Pokémon and carries them off somewhere. Where do they go? Nobody knows.

pokemon.name: buneary
pokemon.text_entry: Buneary can attack by rolling up their ears and then striking with the force created by unrolling them. This attack becomes stronger with training.

pokemon.name: lopunny
pokemon.text_entry: Once hot seasons are over, Lopunny’s coat will be replaced with fur that holds a lot of insulating air in preparation for colder weather.

pokemon.name: mismagius
pokemon.text_entry: Its muttered curses can cause awful headaches or terrifying visions that torment others.

pokemon.name: honchkrow
pokemon.text_entry: Its goons take care of most of the fighting for it. The only time it dirties its own hands is in delivering a final blow to finish off an opponent.

pokemon.name: glameow
pokemon.text_entry: When it’s happy, Glameow demonstrates beautiful movements of its tail, like a dancing ribbon.

pokemon.name: purugly
pokemon.text_entry: To make itself appear intimidatingly beefy, it tightly cinches its waist with its twin tails.

pokemon.name: chingling
pokemon.text_entry: There is an orb inside its mouth. When it hops, the orb bounces all over and makes a ringing sound.

pokemon.name: stunky
pokemon.text_entry: If it lifts its tail and points its rear at you, beware. It’s about to spray you with a fluid stinky enough to make you faint.

pokemon.name: skuntank
pokemon.text_entry: It digs holes in the ground to make its nest. The stench of the fluid it lets fly from the tip of its tail is extremely potent.

pokemon.name: bronzor
pokemon.text_entry: Polishing Bronzor to a shine makes its surface reflect the truth, according to common lore. Be that as it may, Bronzor hates being polished.

pokemon.name: bronzong
pokemon.text_entry: Many scientists suspect that this Pokémon originated outside the Galar region, based on the patterns on its body.

pokemon.name: bonsly
pokemon.text_entry: This Pokémon lives in dry, rocky areas. As its green spheres dry out, their dull luster increases.

pokemon.name: mime-jr
pokemon.text_entry: It looks for a Mr. Rime that’s a good dancer and carefully copies the Mr. Rime’s steps like an apprentice.

pokemon.name: happiny
pokemon.text_entry: Happiny’s willing to lend its precious round stone to those it’s friendly with, but if the stone isn’t returned, Happiny will cry and throw a tantrum.

pokemon.name: chatot
pokemon.text_entry: It can learn and speak human words. If they gather, they all learn the same saying.

pokemon.name: spiritomb
pokemon.text_entry: It was bound to a fissure in an odd keystone as punishment for misdeeds 500 years ago.

pokemon.name: gible
pokemon.text_entry: Its original home is an area much hotter than Alola. If you’re planning to live with one, your heating bill will soar.

pokemon.name: gabite
pokemon.text_entry: It sheds its skin and gradually grows larger. Its scales can be ground into a powder and used as raw materials for traditional medicine.

pokemon.name: garchomp
pokemon.text_entry: Its fine scales don’t just reduce wind resistance—their sharp edges also cause injury to any opponent who attacks it.

pokemon.name: munchlax
pokemon.text_entry: It stores food beneath its fur. It might share just one bite, but only if it really trusts you.

pokemon.name: riolu
pokemon.text_entry: It can use waves called auras to gauge how others are feeling. These same waves can also tell this Pokémon about the state of the environment.

pokemon.name: lucario
pokemon.text_entry: It can tell what people are thinking. Only Trainers who have justice in their hearts can earn this Pokémon’s trust.

pokemon.name: hippopotas
pokemon.text_entry: This Pokémon is active during the day and passes the cold desert nights burrowed snugly into the sand.

pokemon.name: hippowdon
pokemon.text_entry: When roused to violence by its rage, it spews out the quantities of sand it has swallowed and whips up a sandstorm.

pokemon.name: skorupi
pokemon.text_entry: It attacks using the claws on its tail. Once locked in its grip, its prey is unable to move as this Pokémon’s poison seeps in.

pokemon.name: drapion
pokemon.text_entry: It’s so vicious that it’s called the Sand Demon. Yet when confronted by Hippowdon, Drapion keeps a low profile and will never pick a fight.

pokemon.name: croagunk
pokemon.text_entry: Once diluted, its poison becomes medicinal. This Pokémon came into popularity after a pharmaceutical company chose it as a mascot.

pokemon.name: toxicroak
pokemon.text_entry: It booms out a victory croak when its prey goes down in defeat. This Pokémon and Seismitoad are related species.

pokemon.name: carnivine
pokemon.text_entry: It binds itself to trees in marshes. It attracts prey with its sweet-smelling drool and gulps them down.

pokemon.name: finneon
pokemon.text_entry: It lures in prey with its shining tail fins. It stays near the surface during the day and moves to the depths when night falls.

pokemon.name: lumineon
pokemon.text_entry: They traverse the deep waters as if crawling over the seafloor. The fantastic lights of its fins shine like stars in the night sky.

pokemon.name: mantyke
pokemon.text_entry: It swims along with a school of Remoraid, and they’ll all fight together to repel attackers.

pokemon.name: snover
pokemon.text_entry: The berries that grow around its belly are like ice pops. Galarian Darumaka absolutely love these berries.

pokemon.name: abomasnow
pokemon.text_entry: This Pokémon is known to bring blizzards. A shake of its massive body is enough to cause whiteout conditions.

pokemon.name: weavile
pokemon.text_entry: With its claws, it leaves behind signs for its friends to find. The number of distinct signs is said to be over 500.

pokemon.name: magnezone
pokemon.text_entry: It’s thought that a special magnetic field changed the molecular structure of this Pokémon’s body, and that’s what caused the Pokémon’s evolution.

pokemon.name: lickilicky
pokemon.text_entry: Lickilicky can do just about anything with its tongue, which is as dexterous as the human hand. In contrast, Lickilicky’s use of its fingers is clumsy.

pokemon.name: rhyperior
pokemon.text_entry: It relies on its carapace to deflect incoming attacks and throw its enemy off balance. As soon as that happens, it drives its drill into the foe.

pokemon.name: tangrowth
pokemon.text_entry: Vine growth is accelerated for Tangrowth living in warm climates. If the vines grow long, Tangrowth shortens them by tearing parts of them off.

pokemon.name: electivire
pokemon.text_entry: A single Electivire can provide enough electricity for all the buildings in a big city for a year.

pokemon.name: magmortar
pokemon.text_entry: Magmortar takes down its enemies by shooting fireballs, which burn them to a blackened crisp. It avoids this method when hunting prey.

pokemon.name: togekiss
pokemon.text_entry: Known as a bringer of blessings, it’s been depicted on good-luck charms since ancient times.

pokemon.name: yanmega
pokemon.text_entry: This six-legged Pokémon is easily capable of transporting an adult in flight. The wings on its tail help it stay balanced.

pokemon.name: leafeon
pokemon.text_entry: This Pokémon’s tail is blade sharp, with a fantastic cutting edge that can slice right though large trees.

pokemon.name: glaceon
pokemon.text_entry: The coldness emanating from Glaceon causes powdery snow to form, making it quite a popular Pokémon at ski resorts.

pokemon.name: gliscor
pokemon.text_entry: Its flight is soundless. It uses its lengthy tail to carry off its prey... Then its elongated fangs do the rest.

pokemon.name: mamoswine
pokemon.text_entry: It looks strong, and that’s exactly what it is. As the weather grows colder, its ice tusks grow longer, thicker, and more impressive.

pokemon.name: porygon-z
pokemon.text_entry: Some say an additional program made this Pokémon evolve, but even academics can’t agree on whether Porygon-Z is really an evolution.

pokemon.name: gallade
pokemon.text_entry: Sharply attuned to others’ wishes for help, this Pokémon seeks out those in need and aids them in battle.

pokemon.name: probopass
pokemon.text_entry: It uses three small units to catch prey and battle enemies. The main body mostly just gives orders.

pokemon.name: dusknoir
pokemon.text_entry: With the mouth on its belly, Dusknoir swallows its target whole. The soul is the only thing eaten— Dusknoir disgorges the body before departing.

pokemon.name: froslass
pokemon.text_entry: It spits out cold air of nearly −60 degrees Fahrenheit to freeze its quarry. It brings frozen prey back to its lair and neatly lines them up.

pokemon.name: rotom
pokemon.text_entry: With a body made of plasma, it can inhabit all sorts of machines. It loves to surprise others.

pokemon.name: uxie
pokemon.text_entry: It is said that its emergence gave humans the intelligence to improve their quality of life.

pokemon.name: mesprit
pokemon.text_entry: It sleeps at the bottom of a lake. Its spirit is said to leave its body to fly on the lake’s surface.

pokemon.name: azelf
pokemon.text_entry: It is thought that Uxie, Mesprit, and Azelf all came from the same egg.

pokemon.name: dialga
pokemon.text_entry: It has the power to control time. It appears in Sinnoh-region myths as an ancient deity.

pokemon.name: palkia
pokemon.text_entry: It has the ability to distort space. It is described as a deity in Sinnoh-region mythology.

pokemon.name: heatran
pokemon.text_entry: Boiling blood, like magma, circulates through its body. It makes its dwelling place in volcanic caves.

pokemon.name: regigigas
pokemon.text_entry: There is an enduring legend that states this Pokémon towed continents with ropes.

pokemon.name: giratina-altered
pokemon.text_entry: It was banished for its violence. It silently gazed upon the old world from the Distortion World.

pokemon.name: cresselia
pokemon.text_entry: Those who sleep holding Cresselia’s feather are assured of joyful dreams. It is said to represent the crescent moon.

pokemon.name: phione
pokemon.text_entry: It drifts in warm seas. It always returns to where it was born, no matter how far it may have drifted.

pokemon.name: manaphy
pokemon.text_entry: It starts its life with a wondrous power that permits it to bond with any kind of Pokémon.

pokemon.name: darkrai
pokemon.text_entry: It can lull people to sleep and make them dream. It is active during nights of the new moon.

pokemon.name: shaymin-land
pokemon.text_entry: The blooming of Gracidea flowers confers the power of flight upon it. Feelings of gratitude are the message it delivers.

pokemon.name: arceus
pokemon.text_entry: It is told in mythology that this Pokémon was born before the universe even existed.
